    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Cumberland</placeName>
                <date>June 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser Esq</addressee>:</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear sir: We <sic>belief</sic><lb/> it is interesting to you to hear
                some times some<lb/> thing about the <sic>wellfare</sic> &amp; improving
                con<lb/>dition of small congregations such as ours:<lb/> it gives me pleasure to
                assure you that we<lb/> are spiritually &amp; <sic>finanzicaly</sic> prospering<lb/>
                <sic>thoug</sic> there may be some indifferent ones,<lb/> the majority of our
                    Cahl<add>?</add> are good determined<lb/> Jews whom nought could induce to
                fall<lb/> back to the death like sleep of indifference.<lb/> By Order of our
                President <persName>Mr S. Herdellerger</persName><lb/>, elected may last., I am to
                inform you that our<lb/> Congregation is compelled to engage another<lb/> gentleman
                to fill the vacancy of Chasan Shochet<lb/> &amp; Teacher occasioned by the timely
                resignation of<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Wechsler</persName> our present functionary, as also<lb/> to advertise
                in differen'd papers we have<lb/> agreed with <persName>Mr W.</persName> that he
                will give up<lb/> the place at any time from the <date>first of August</date><lb/>
                or earlier otherwise continue his functions a<lb/> month after expiration of the
                Quarter being<lb/> to the <date>first of October</date> in case we are not able<lb/>
                to fill the vacancy sooner. A single<lb/> man</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>man one of those generally emigrating from
                <placeName><sic>germany</sic></placeName><lb/> to this <sic>contry</sic> we prefer
                as expectation of such don't<lb/> overreact our ability, we pay 250.00 doll. you
                will<lb/> please to insert in the Occident a Notice in general<lb/> that on
                application to <persName>Frank</persName> &amp; <persName role="author"
                    >Adler</persName> further<lb/> particulars will be given, and charge to the
                congregation<lb/> The accounts of the <sic>suffrings</sic> of our Brethren in<lb/>
                <placeName>Erez Israel</placeName> have reached us, and <sic>dreadfull</sic><lb/>
                &amp; <sic>heartsickning</sic>
                <sic>the</sic> are indeed. An Appeal made<lb/> to our brethren <sic>hier</sic> was
                heartily <sic>respondet</sic><lb/> to and from the result we are glad to send<lb/>
                to you, the agent, the enclosed Draft for 50 dol<lb/> on the western Bank of Balto.
                may this, little as it<lb/> is, contribute to alleviate such distress.</p>
            <p>we fail the monthly appearance of your Occident<lb/> and swarming as this
                    <sic>country</sic> is with proselyte<lb/> scrip, it cannot fail to refresh &amp;
                strengthen<lb/> the mind of every israelitish reader, hoping<lb/> that you enjoy
                good health, we take the<lb/> liberty to sign <sic>ourselfs</sic> your sincere
                friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Henry Adler</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Secty of the <add>?</add> B. L Congregation</p>
        </body>
